Eucalyptus semota, commonly known as marymia mallee, is a mallee tree that is native to central Western Australia.The mallee or tree typically grows to a height of 2 to 9 metres (7 to 30 ft) and mostly has smooth bark with a stocking of rough peeling bark at the base. It blooms between July and December producing inflorescences with white-cream-yellow flowers.
It is found among quartz outcrops in the Mid West and Goldfields-Esperance regions between Meekatharra and Wiluna where it grows in clay soils.
